WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.400
[ Festive music plays ]

00:02.402 --> 00:04.002
Anyway,
it was not the "Rocky II"

00:04.004 --> 00:05.203
I thought it was
when I rented it.

00:05.205 --> 00:07.872
Cher wasn't even in it.
Rip-off!

00:07.874 --> 00:09.541
Yeah, get -- go eat
that somewhere else.

00:09.543 --> 00:13.211
Season's greetings,
Smoot faculty! [ Laughs ]

00:13.213 --> 00:16.414
Now, I have some news that,
when you hear it,

00:16.416 --> 00:19.551
I think "yule"
be quite merry.

00:19.553 --> 00:22.154
[ Laughs ] Y-u-l-e.
I get it!

00:22.156 --> 00:23.221
Steven got it.

00:23.223 --> 00:24.489
Anyways, the big news is,

00:24.491 --> 00:28.226
I was able to squeeze $400
out of the budget

00:28.228 --> 00:29.628
and put it towards

00:29.630 --> 00:33.498
a Smoot outdoor
Christmas lights display!

00:33.500 --> 00:35.700
Quinn,
it's<i> holiday</i> display.

00:35.702 --> 00:37.636
This is a public school.
We should be inclusive.

00:37.638 --> 00:40.238
Okay, thank you, Abbey,
for getting involved.

00:40.240 --> 00:41.440
Uh, I'm just saying that,

00:41.442 --> 00:43.509
if we play
our Christmas cards...

00:44.445 --> 00:46.378
...holiday cards right,

00:46.380 --> 00:50.114
we have a chance to be featured
in the Channel 5 News

00:50.116 --> 00:54.987
"12 Weeks of Holiday Lights"
contest! [ Laughs ]

00:54.989 --> 00:56.388
Have you guys seen this?

00:56.390 --> 00:58.590
I was just talking to some
cool kids smoking cigarettes,

00:58.592 --> 00:59.992
and they say we need
to raise money stat

00:59.994 --> 01:02.060
because Marcus needs
a new heart transplant.

01:02.062 --> 01:03.195
-What?
-What?

01:03.197 --> 01:04.463
Marcus, the frail
little sophomore kid?

01:04.465 --> 01:06.999
Marcus may be frail,
but he has an upbeat attitude

01:07.001 --> 01:09.401
and an unfailing love
of hip-hop, Steven.

01:09.403 --> 01:11.536
It's not his fault
he has a pigeon-sized heart.

01:11.538 --> 01:13.138
What?
I've never heard of that.
That is a gigantic heart.

01:13.140 --> 01:16.274
-Pigeons can be up to 8 pounds.
-Idiots!

01:16.276 --> 01:17.742
No, no, no.
I said it wrong.
I'm not a doctor.

01:17.744 --> 01:20.745
His heart is the size
of a heart of a pigeon.

01:20.747 --> 01:22.815
-Oh! That's opposite.
-Oh. They're so tiny!

01:22.817 --> 01:24.082
His family's raising money

01:24.084 --> 01:25.750
with a
WhyDon'tYouGoFundYourself page,

01:25.752 --> 01:28.286
but they only know
other poor people.

01:28.288 --> 01:30.622
After 15 long years,

01:30.624 --> 01:34.226
looks like Marcus' little pigeon
heart is finally about to --

01:34.228 --> 01:37.896
[ Steady beep ]

01:37.898 --> 01:41.299
Oh! Yeah, that's me.
Damn it!

01:41.301 --> 01:43.968
That's Tampa's
38-week ultrasound.

01:43.970 --> 01:47.772
I'm sorry. I got to
get out of here, guys.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.441
He can't
just leave school.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.709
[ Festive music plays ]

01:50.711 --> 01:53.178
♪ Quit wasting my time ♪

01:53.180 --> 01:55.580
♪ I ain't here for you ♪

01:55.582 --> 01:57.982
♪ I'm just putting in work ♪

01:57.984 --> 02:03.522
♪ Till my day is through ♪

02:03.524 --> 02:06.058
You guys, this could be
Marcus' last Christmas.

02:06.060 --> 02:07.860
I hope it's better
than my last Christmas.

02:07.862 --> 02:09.327
I didn't get anything
I asked for.

02:09.329 --> 02:10.795
Here's a thought --

02:10.797 --> 02:12.797
what if we took
that $400

02:12.799 --> 02:14.399
and put it towards
helping out Marcus?

02:14.401 --> 02:15.467
-Yes!
-That's great!

02:15.469 --> 02:16.468
-That's great.
-Yeah.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.002
$400 is a lot of money.

02:18.004 --> 02:19.738
However, you want to get
that kid a heart --

02:19.740 --> 02:21.005
and I mean a real heart...

02:21.007 --> 02:22.340
Yes, the best heart!

02:22.342 --> 02:24.676
...use that money
to make money.

02:24.678 --> 02:25.744
[ Papers thump softly ]

02:25.746 --> 02:26.945
-Bake sale style!
-Bake sale!

02:26.947 --> 02:28.012
-Yes!
-That's a great idea.

02:28.014 --> 02:29.281
-There you go.
-I love it.

02:29.283 --> 02:31.750
Bake sale.
I'm a master baker.
I'll whip up a batch.

02:31.752 --> 02:33.952
Here's hoping
for a holiday miracle.
Yes!

02:33.954 --> 02:36.088
Actually, "miracle"
is kind of loaded.

02:36.090 --> 02:38.223
Abbey! Agh!

02:38.225 --> 02:41.093
Thank you so much
for reminding me!

02:41.095 --> 02:45.163
Ugh!
Here's hoping for a...

02:45.165 --> 02:49.568
Smoot Holiday
"Coincidence"!

02:49.570 --> 02:51.103
Yes!

02:51.105 --> 02:52.637
♪♪

02:52.639 --> 02:53.772
I just don't understand.

02:53.774 --> 02:54.773
Give it better real estate,
and they'll move more.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.575
It's literally in
the center of the table.

02:56.577 --> 02:58.376
Can I get
one reindeer cookie

02:58.378 --> 02:59.978
and two Christmas tree
cookies, please?

02:59.980 --> 03:02.447
You can have one
Kwanzaa wildebeest cookie

03:02.449 --> 03:05.250
and two winter solstice
green triangles.

03:05.252 --> 03:07.319
Absolutely!
Happy Holidays!

03:07.321 --> 03:08.653
Thanks.

03:08.655 --> 03:10.122
Hey, everybody, there he is.
There he is!

03:10.124 --> 03:12.190
Look, everybody!
There's our guy!

03:12.192 --> 03:13.926
Round of applause
for Marcus!

03:13.928 --> 03:15.794
[ Applause ]

03:15.796 --> 03:17.796
Aw, damn, y'all!
This is all for me?

03:17.798 --> 03:19.998
[ Scoffs ] You bet your ass
it's for you, Marcus.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.134
Y'all be all right.
For real, though.

03:22.136 --> 03:24.136
Pigeon heart?
It's more like pidgin English.

03:24.138 --> 03:25.737
Is it too late to get
my cookie money back?

03:25.739 --> 03:27.672
Stop that! He's right
in front of you.

03:27.674 --> 03:29.207
Marcus, I want you
to eat up, buddy.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.742
Put some meat
on those bones.
Yeah.

03:30.744 --> 03:33.211
Anything you want,
free of charge.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.546
-Within reason, kid.
-Come on.

03:34.548 --> 03:36.348
I'll take a white star,
man.

03:36.350 --> 03:39.818
Non-denominational star.
You bet your ass he is.

03:39.820 --> 03:43.021
[ Festive music plays ]

03:43.023 --> 03:44.556
Woman: $1,746...

03:44.558 --> 03:46.425
Together:
...$1,747...

03:46.427 --> 03:48.893
and $1,748!

03:48.895 --> 03:50.295
-You kidding me?
-That's it!

03:50.297 --> 03:52.564
-That is outstanding!
-See? I told you!

03:52.566 --> 03:55.233
That's a 200% increase
on Quinn's seed money,

03:55.235 --> 03:57.369
and that's
even after my cut.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.704
Your what?
Oh, I'm sorry.
I must have misspoke.

03:59.706 --> 04:03.107
What I meant to say
was "after my cut"!

04:03.109 --> 04:05.243
These blowouts don't pay
for themselves, you know.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.179
-Real nice. Real nice.
-1...2...

04:07.181 --> 04:10.515
All right, tell the pigeon kid
I said good luck.

04:10.517 --> 04:13.585
You know what? We should quit
our jobs and just do bake sales.

04:13.587 --> 04:15.920
I'll say.
That's a lot of "dough."

04:15.922 --> 04:17.522
Come on, Steven.

04:17.524 --> 04:18.791
-Steven.
-[ Sighs ]

04:18.793 --> 04:20.325
Congrats, guys.
Job well done.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.593
Yeah, you, too, Steven.
Thanks for your help, bud.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.128
Abbey: Yeah,
the cupcakes were great.

04:23.130 --> 04:26.665
Hey, yo, Marcus.
14 hundo, dawg.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.066
Don't spend it all
in one place.

04:28.068 --> 04:30.335
Wait. Actually, definitely
spend it in one place --

04:30.337 --> 04:31.336
all on the heart
transplant, okay?

04:31.338 --> 04:32.805
Yo, Mr. P.,

04:32.807 --> 04:34.606
that was dope as hell
of all the teachers.

04:34.608 --> 04:35.874
Well, yeah. Yeah.

04:35.876 --> 04:38.811
But the doctor says
my surgery costs 15 G's.

04:38.813 --> 04:39.944
15 G's?

04:39.946 --> 04:42.080
And my mom already sold
all her stuff.

04:42.082 --> 04:44.483
God damn, Marcus.

04:44.485 --> 04:47.152
Give me that money back
right now, Marcus.
What?

04:47.154 --> 04:48.687
-Give it back!
-No!

04:48.689 --> 04:49.888
Marcus,
there will be plenty more

04:49.890 --> 04:51.289
where this came from,
okay?

04:51.291 --> 04:52.357
-I don't want you worrying --
-[ Coughs ]

04:52.359 --> 04:54.292
Sorry. Sorry.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.361
I don't want you worrying
your little bird-sized heart

04:56.363 --> 04:58.497
about money anymore --
that's not for you.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.433
That's for adults
with regular-sized hearts.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.101
Your job
is to be a teenager.

05:03.103 --> 05:05.170
You just go out there,
and you keeping YOLO-ing.

05:05.172 --> 05:08.907
YOLO. Yeah,
that'd be really cool.

05:08.909 --> 05:09.908
YOLO.

05:09.910 --> 05:10.909
Get out there, son.

05:10.911 --> 05:12.711
[ Coughs ]
Sorry.

05:12.713 --> 05:15.914
Dangerous Danishes.
I must have had five or six.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.449
Okay, so it turns out

05:17.451 --> 05:20.318
$1,400 doesn't buy
a heart transplant

05:20.320 --> 05:21.786
in this shit town anymore.

05:21.788 --> 05:23.388
-We need 15,000 bucks.
-What?!

05:23.390 --> 05:24.723
-What?
-The crooks!

05:24.725 --> 05:26.725
It's this new Denver.
[ Chuckles ]

05:26.727 --> 05:29.928
We got to turn this $1,400
into $15,000 somehow.

05:29.930 --> 05:31.996
Okay, well, Loren, I appreciate
your bond with Marcus

05:31.998 --> 05:33.798
and your
situational altruism,

05:33.800 --> 05:36.068
but we've made
a significant contribution.

05:36.070 --> 05:38.203
I mean, our bake sale
got them 10% of the way there.

05:38.205 --> 05:39.672
Hey, maybe you haven't been
paying attention, Steven,

05:39.674 --> 05:42.274
but for Marcus,
10% of the goal means 100% --

05:42.276 --> 05:45.009
[ Steady beep ]
Oh, yeah. Mm-hmm.

05:45.011 --> 05:46.144
That's you again.

05:46.146 --> 05:48.012
Oh, God! It is!

05:48.014 --> 05:48.947
Ugh!

05:48.949 --> 05:50.282
[ Beeping stops ]

05:50.284 --> 05:53.218
Tampa again. Prenatal yoga now.
[ Scoffs ]

05:53.220 --> 05:54.486
I don't even know
how she's gonna do it.

05:54.488 --> 05:57.556
Her pelvic floor
is decimated!

05:57.558 --> 06:00.425
Now, who here has the balls
to help me fundraise

06:00.427 --> 06:02.361
before Steven
literally kills Marcus?

06:02.363 --> 06:04.829
Okay, I hesitate
to bring this up,

06:04.831 --> 06:06.965
but when I was at Choate,
we had charity auctions,

06:06.967 --> 06:08.300
and they were
quite effective.

06:08.302 --> 06:09.902
I think, if we did something
simple and understated --

06:09.904 --> 06:11.703
Black-tie gala! I love that!
I love that idea!

06:11.705 --> 06:12.771
-Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!
-Okay.

06:12.773 --> 06:13.772
Steven is right!
Steven is right!

06:13.774 --> 06:15.039
You have to spend money
to make money!

06:15.041 --> 06:16.241
No, no, no. That's not
what I'm talking about.

06:16.243 --> 06:17.642
-But we go big with this thing.
-Love that idea.

06:17.644 --> 06:19.644
Calm down.
On top of that,
we can donate items,

06:19.646 --> 06:21.380
and it would be great
to have an excuse

06:21.382 --> 06:23.047
to get dressed up
around here.

06:23.049 --> 06:24.182
Oh, I know exactly
what I'm wearing!

06:24.184 --> 06:25.183
Okay, you know,
we got to keep in mind,

06:25.185 --> 06:27.119
we only have a budget
of $1,400.

06:27.121 --> 06:29.187
-Right.
-I know it's a long shot,

06:29.189 --> 06:31.323
but I'm willing to bet
that's what

06:31.325 --> 06:34.393
old Mike and Barb Peterson
thought, too.

06:35.996 --> 06:37.262
Hello?

06:37.264 --> 06:39.798
Winner of last year's
Burt Crandall's

06:39.800 --> 06:43.135
"12 Weeks
of Holiday Lights" contest!

06:43.137 --> 06:46.471
No one here knows who
I'm talking about? No one?

06:46.473 --> 06:49.741
Quinn is right.
That was a long shot.

06:49.743 --> 06:51.075
And after all, you guys,

06:51.077 --> 06:52.877
what is the real meaning
of Christmas?

06:52.879 --> 06:54.346
-Kill or be killed!
-Grip it and rip it.

06:54.348 --> 06:55.547
-Close.
-You burn it to the ground...

06:55.549 --> 06:56.748
That is not the meaning
of Christmas, guys.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.082
...and you make
them beg for mercy!

06:58.084 --> 06:59.351
Well, I'll tell you what --
this might just end up

06:59.353 --> 07:02.086
turning into
a Smoot Christmas Miracle!

07:02.088 --> 07:04.089
-Yes!
-Okay, Abbey.

07:04.091 --> 07:07.693
Sorry,
a Smoot Holiday Coincidence.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.397
Steven:
Wow, I have to say,

07:12.399 --> 07:14.599
you guys pulled off
an incredible transformation.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.268
Well, you were wrong
to doubt us, Steven.

07:16.270 --> 07:18.737
You know, we may not be
some fancy boarding school,

07:18.739 --> 07:21.473
but when we want to, we can
just straight-up shit class.

07:21.475 --> 07:22.474
Ooh! Pizza rolls.

07:22.476 --> 07:23.475
-Ooh!
-Yes.

07:23.477 --> 07:25.077
Well, I know
the students helped out,

07:25.079 --> 07:26.745
but how'd you get
so many things donated?

07:26.747 --> 07:29.081
I mean, the champagne, the
catering, the ice sculpture...

07:29.083 --> 07:30.815
People donate anything
for the right price.

07:30.817 --> 07:32.951
Plus, Quinn gave everyone access
to the Smoot credit card,

07:32.953 --> 07:34.152
so we're good.

07:34.154 --> 07:35.754
You think that we may have gone
over budget a bit?

07:35.756 --> 07:37.356
-Seriously, chill out.
-Don't worry. Come on!

07:37.358 --> 07:38.490
-Enjoy the night!
-All right!

07:38.492 --> 07:40.158
[ Laughs ]

07:40.160 --> 07:41.560
-He's so uptight.
-What a stick in the mud.

07:41.562 --> 07:43.161
When have we ever
blown anything?

07:43.163 --> 07:44.829
Oh! Glad I made it!

07:44.831 --> 07:47.499
Oh, wow! Look at this place!
[ Chuckles ]

07:47.501 --> 07:48.967
Shoemaker,
chips and salsa?

07:48.969 --> 07:50.969
What, do you think this is --
your son's T-ball game?

07:50.971 --> 07:52.371
This is
New York City salsa.

07:52.373 --> 07:53.505
-New York City?!
-New York City?!

07:53.507 --> 07:55.774
It's artisanal.
It's from Brooklyn.

07:55.776 --> 07:57.175
Okay, I hope
your auction item

07:57.177 --> 07:58.977
is a bit more upscale,
Shoemaker.

07:58.979 --> 08:01.513
In case you haven't noticed,
this is a high-end event.

08:01.515 --> 08:03.181
-Dealin' Dave is here.
-Yeah.

08:03.183 --> 08:05.117
What?!
The used car baron?

08:05.119 --> 08:07.119
I've gone to prison
twice.

08:07.121 --> 08:08.653
Now, I don't know
if that gets in the way

08:08.655 --> 08:09.722
of trying to get a car...

08:09.724 --> 08:10.923
-Excuse me.
-Okay.

08:10.925 --> 08:13.058
Oh, man! I'm sorry.

08:13.060 --> 08:16.395
I-I've just been so just
caught up with this baby thing.

08:16.397 --> 08:18.196
I-I haven't had time
to do anything.

08:18.198 --> 08:20.064
-Typical right-wing bullshit.
-Mm-hmm.

08:20.066 --> 08:22.667
More concerned about
the welfare of an unborn child

08:22.669 --> 08:24.603
than the dying child
right here in front of us.

08:24.605 --> 08:27.272
Yeah. Get it together
before the auction, Shoemaker.

08:27.274 --> 08:29.341
-You're a monster.
-These are really good.

08:29.343 --> 08:31.143
Have you tried
the lamb meatballs?

08:31.145 --> 08:32.144
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

08:32.146 --> 08:33.946
[ Slow festive music plays ]

08:33.948 --> 08:35.347
Oh!

08:35.349 --> 08:37.081
[ Feedback whines, tapping ]

08:37.083 --> 08:39.418
That's on. Okay!
Here we go, folks.

08:39.420 --> 08:45.290
Welcome, everyone,
to An Evening for Marcus.

08:45.292 --> 08:47.025
We're gonna have
some fun tonight.

08:47.027 --> 08:49.762
Oh! Let's rip it wide open.
Here we go.

08:49.764 --> 08:52.030
Our first item up for bid
was donated

08:52.032 --> 08:55.434
by Smoot High School's
very own Abbey Logan.

08:55.436 --> 08:56.835
Abbey, get out here!

08:56.837 --> 08:59.571
What Abbey has donated --
This is neat.

08:59.573 --> 09:03.708
It's a "Library Ride Along"
experience.

09:03.710 --> 09:04.777
So you'd spend the day

09:04.779 --> 09:07.646
amidst the thrilling sights
and sounds

09:07.648 --> 09:10.315
of the Smoot Library.

09:10.317 --> 09:12.384
Let's open up the floor
for bidding.

09:12.386 --> 09:15.520
[ Chuckles ]
Let's start at, uh, $4.

09:15.522 --> 09:17.055
Anyone?

09:17.057 --> 09:18.657
Man: $800!

09:18.659 --> 09:21.593
-Sold!
-[ Chuckles ] See?

09:21.595 --> 09:24.329
It's me!
Danny Trebin!

09:24.331 --> 09:27.131
Hello, faculty member
Dan Trebin!
No.

09:27.133 --> 09:29.334
We have two spectacular

09:29.336 --> 09:32.337
Terrestrial Seasonings
gift baskets!

09:32.339 --> 09:33.405
Coach Fairbell

09:33.407 --> 09:36.341
has, uh, donated
some of his favorites

09:36.343 --> 09:39.478
from his collection
of rare and unusual toys.

09:39.480 --> 09:42.481
A day of free I.T. help!

09:42.483 --> 09:46.551
Mr. Payton is offering
a producer's credit

09:46.553 --> 09:48.620
on Marcus'
upcoming rap album,

09:48.622 --> 09:51.756
which is features on
and also produces.

09:51.758 --> 09:53.425
Mm!

09:53.427 --> 09:56.361
Yo, this track is called
"Fucket List."

