Identity theft --

10:25.259 --> 10:26.725
-I'm good at that.
-You can get identity --

10:26.727 --> 10:27.992
You can prevent someone
from getting your identity.

10:27.994 --> 10:29.994
She's willing --
You can take
someone's identity.

10:29.996 --> 10:32.264
Sold!
[ Applause ]

10:32.266 --> 10:34.799
You're getting
a hand-woven basket!

10:34.801 --> 10:37.936
Someone made this! $150!

10:37.938 --> 10:40.138
Folks, I think we're still
not playing hardball yet!

10:40.140 --> 10:41.540
-Oh, my God!
-No!

10:41.542 --> 10:43.075
-What is that?!
-No!

10:43.077 --> 10:44.543
This is
a Rocky Dennis doll!

10:44.545 --> 10:45.678
-Oh!
-It's not for sale!

10:45.680 --> 10:47.612
I don't even know
how he got in the box!

10:47.614 --> 10:49.614
-1,200 bucks!
-$1,200. Sold. Leslie.

10:49.616 --> 10:51.149
Fantastic.
No, wait!
No, he's not for sale!

10:51.151 --> 10:52.284
Yes, he is!
She just bought him!

10:52.286 --> 10:54.018
-No! He's mine!
-No, he's not!

10:54.020 --> 10:56.154
-Leslie, get him!
-That's my doll!

10:56.156 --> 10:57.622
Give me that, you freak!

10:57.624 --> 10:58.757
[ Calling ]

10:58.759 --> 11:00.158
Anybody on the left side,
on the right side?

11:00.160 --> 11:01.293
Going once, going twice!

11:01.295 --> 11:03.828
Hey, did your wife get those
free from work, Sweens?

11:03.830 --> 11:05.364
Sold, $205!

11:05.366 --> 11:07.299
Oh, I'm not -- I'm not bidding.
I'm heckling.

11:07.301 --> 11:09.834
♪♪

11:09.836 --> 11:13.505
If there's one thing
that I've learned from the...

11:13.507 --> 11:15.707
[ Feedback whines ]

11:15.709 --> 11:18.777
...from the story
of the first Christmas,

11:18.779 --> 11:21.513
it's to go big or go home!

11:21.515 --> 11:25.317
So I will be auctioning off

11:25.319 --> 11:30.522
the right to name
my unborn child!

11:30.524 --> 11:31.523
[ Feedback whines ]

11:31.525 --> 11:33.726
[ Audience murmurs,
light applause ]

11:33.728 --> 11:36.061
How about $50?

11:36.063 --> 11:38.330
Okay. Do we have $55?

11:38.332 --> 11:39.664
-$55!
-Whoa!

11:39.666 --> 11:41.466
-Do I have $65?
-There it is.

11:41.468 --> 11:43.268
-$500!
-What?!

11:43.270 --> 11:45.938
-$500, sold to Dealin' Dave!
-Boom!

11:45.940 --> 11:47.472
Local celebrity!

11:47.474 --> 11:50.409
Located on Brighton Boulevard,
Denver, Colorado.

11:50.411 --> 11:52.076
-Just past the Coliseum.
-Hey.

11:52.078 --> 11:54.212
We had a couple ideas
in mind for a boy.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.147
Agh!

11:55.149 --> 11:56.949
[ Thuds ]
[ All gasping ]

11:56.951 --> 11:59.551
Yeah, they only made
43 of these babies

11:59.553 --> 12:02.220
till the
Parental Advisory Council

12:02.222 --> 12:03.888
took them off the market.

12:03.890 --> 12:05.157
Apparently,
kids were cuddling,

12:05.159 --> 12:07.960
and their faces were getting
ripped up by the braces.

12:07.962 --> 12:09.094
All right.

12:09.096 --> 12:10.695
Can I just
give it one more hug?

12:10.697 --> 12:14.499
Oh, don't you have some other
weird shit at home to hug?

12:14.501 --> 12:15.700
Not like Rock!

12:15.702 --> 12:17.569
All right. [ Chuckles ]
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

12:17.571 --> 12:19.104
It's over $15,000!
Oh, my God! Yes!

12:19.106 --> 12:21.039
-Whoa!
-Ha ha!

12:21.041 --> 12:22.775
[ Cellphone chimes ]
That's what
I'm talking about!

12:22.777 --> 12:24.108
-Good job, man!
-[ Laughs ]

12:24.110 --> 12:25.444
[ Applause ]
Man: What are we applauding?

12:25.446 --> 12:28.246
Quinn:
It's the credit card company.

12:28.248 --> 12:32.050
Did you people charge over
10 grand to throw this gala?

12:32.052 --> 12:33.852
-What? God.
-No. Absolutely not.

12:33.854 --> 12:37.656
I specifically said
we had a budget of $1,400.

12:37.658 --> 12:39.324
Yeah.
And that's
exactly what I spent.

12:39.326 --> 12:40.659
-I spent $1,400.
-Yeah, me, too.

12:40.661 --> 12:42.327
That was $400.
That was $700.

12:42.329 --> 12:44.196
Not $1,400<i> each.</i>

12:44.198 --> 12:45.530
-Ohh.
-Oh.

12:45.532 --> 12:46.931
That's something
we should have clarified

12:46.933 --> 12:48.066
prior to any of this.

12:48.068 --> 12:52.004
Oh. Okay.
We netted $5,000.

12:52.006 --> 12:54.272
-God. No!
-[ Sighs ]

12:54.274 --> 12:56.140
Wait a second.
$15,000 --

12:56.142 --> 12:58.943
That is the exact
grand prize amount

12:58.945 --> 13:01.346
for Burt Crandall's "12 Weeks
of Holiday Lights" contest!

13:01.348 --> 13:02.414
-What?!
-What?!

13:02.416 --> 13:03.948
Wait.
Why didn't you tell us

13:03.950 --> 13:05.684
about the prize money
before we did this auction?

13:05.686 --> 13:09.221
Well, because that's not what
the contest is about, Abbey!

13:09.223 --> 13:10.889
Let's do it!
Let's let it ride!

13:10.891 --> 13:12.691
Let's take this $5,000

13:12.693 --> 13:15.694
and turn it into a beautiful
twinkling strand of 15 large!

13:15.696 --> 13:17.162
-Yes! Yes!
-We can do this!

13:17.164 --> 13:18.563
-We can do this!
-Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

13:18.565 --> 13:20.833
-What?
-You are betting Marcus' life

13:20.835 --> 13:23.568
on whether
or not Burt Crandall

13:23.570 --> 13:24.903
likes our Christmas lights
or not?

13:24.905 --> 13:27.039
Yeah.
I could not have
said it better myself.

13:27.041 --> 13:28.507
That is a horrible idea.

13:28.509 --> 13:30.375
You know what, Steven?

13:30.377 --> 13:33.512
I'm tired of you
and your war on Christmas.

13:33.514 --> 13:35.580
-Hey! No, that's what it is.
-That's not fair.

13:35.582 --> 13:37.115
-Yes, it is.
-Enough!

13:37.117 --> 13:39.184
If there's one thing
I've learned from Jesus Christ,

13:39.186 --> 13:41.253
it's that one guy
with 12 friends

13:41.255 --> 13:43.188
who don't ask
any questions --

13:43.190 --> 13:44.256
they can accomplish
anything.

13:44.258 --> 13:46.659
-Whoa, look at that.
-Look at Marcus.

13:46.661 --> 13:47.926
Loren:
Look at the heart on this kid.

13:47.928 --> 13:49.928
-Pigeon-sized, my ass.
-Mm.

13:49.930 --> 13:52.665
Marcus, buddy, you don't
have to clean up.

13:52.667 --> 13:54.132
I just want to help.

13:54.134 --> 13:56.201
Nobody ever done anything
like this for me.

13:56.203 --> 13:59.204
Well, I got some news for you --
we're not done yet, okay?

13:59.206 --> 14:01.740
So you just go out there
and YOLO like I to'd-yo.

14:01.742 --> 14:04.476
Suck the marrow out of
every last day you have, bud.

14:04.478 --> 14:05.744
YOLO, bud.

14:05.746 --> 14:07.680
Y'all are crazy --

14:07.682 --> 14:08.881
crazy nice.

14:08.883 --> 14:10.215
[ Laughter ]

14:10.217 --> 14:12.284
Well, we better
get decorating.
Yeah.

14:12.286 --> 14:15.087
This is gonna be
a Smoot Holiday Coincidence!

14:15.089 --> 14:16.221
[ Chuckles ]
[ Coughs ]

14:16.223 --> 14:17.289
-Oh, geez.
-Oh, God!

14:17.291 --> 14:18.490
I got you, bud.
I got you.

14:18.492 --> 14:20.425
God bless, y'all!

14:20.427 --> 14:21.560
All y'all.

14:23.296 --> 14:26.164
37,000 lights.

14:26.166 --> 14:28.100
Two backup generators.

14:28.102 --> 14:30.569
100 wreaths.
That should be 200.

14:30.571 --> 14:31.904
Looking good, Geoffrey.

14:31.906 --> 14:33.238
Oh, thank you.
I tell you what --

14:33.240 --> 14:35.374
when meteorologist
Burt Crandall sees this,

14:35.376 --> 14:37.442
he will not be
disappointed.

14:37.444 --> 14:38.843
♪♪

14:38.845 --> 14:40.312
[ Horn honks ]

14:40.314 --> 14:42.114
[ Chuckling ] Oh! Sweens.

14:42.116 --> 14:44.849
Rockin' the convertible
in 47 degrees, huh?

14:44.851 --> 14:46.384
Bold choice.

14:46.386 --> 14:49.121
Mr. Payton, when the sun
comes out, the top goes down.
Nope.

14:49.123 --> 14:50.789
Listen, I was thinking
about what you were saying,

14:50.791 --> 14:53.458
and, uh, perhaps
I did overlook Marcus a bit,

14:53.460 --> 14:55.393
and it wouldn't be
the holiday season

14:55.395 --> 14:56.995
if I didn't go
a step further.

14:56.997 --> 14:59.531
So you're gonna give him the car
from "Stuart Little." Cool.

14:59.533 --> 15:01.066
Ha, ha, very funny.

15:01.068 --> 15:02.401
I was listening to that rap
he was doing

15:02.403 --> 15:03.868
about his bucket list,

15:03.870 --> 15:05.738
and I was thinking
I would take him for a spin

15:05.740 --> 15:07.606
in a classic Miata,
you know?

15:07.608 --> 15:10.008
Let him feel the exhilaration
of four cylinders.

15:10.010 --> 15:11.076
Well, yeah.

15:11.078 --> 15:13.678
Well, thanks
for coming around, Sweens.

15:13.680 --> 15:16.148
You know,
in a different world,

15:16.150 --> 15:18.483
I could really see
you and me being friends.

15:18.485 --> 15:21.353
But these were the cards
we were dealt, so, you know...

15:21.355 --> 15:23.155
[ Festive music plays ]

15:23.157 --> 15:26.691
Okay. Oh, my God!
What the hell is this?

15:26.693 --> 15:29.361
This is an inclusive,
non-denominational
nativity scene.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.896
No, it's not.
This is the nativity scene

15:31.898 --> 15:33.898
from the front window
of an Old Navy.

15:33.900 --> 15:35.433
I'm sorry if I don't
want to participate

15:35.435 --> 15:37.970
in shoving a belief system
down people's throats.

15:37.972 --> 15:42.374
Okay, so you decided to put
an American flag hijab

15:42.376 --> 15:44.042
on a wise man

15:44.044 --> 15:45.778
at the birth
of what appears to be

15:45.780 --> 15:47.512
a Native American
Jesus Christ.

15:47.514 --> 15:49.047
-Yeah? Why not?
-Oh, I don't know.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.248
Let's start with
a couple reasons here.

15:50.250 --> 15:51.516
Oh, I'd love to hear them.

15:51.518 --> 15:53.718
One, there wasn't
a United States of America.

15:53.720 --> 15:56.454
Two, there wasn't
even an Islam!

15:56.456 --> 15:58.523
You know, they have
a word in Japan

15:58.525 --> 16:00.725
for the experience
of driving a Miata.

16:00.727 --> 16:02.194
It's "Jinba Ittai,"

16:02.196 --> 16:04.396
which means "the rider
and the horse are one."

16:04.398 --> 16:06.398
Yeah. No, that's
a real sweet ride.

16:06.400 --> 16:08.400
[ Clicks tongue ]
Maybe I'll get one someday.

16:08.402 --> 16:10.669
♪♪

16:10.671 --> 16:12.871
[ Gearshift clicks ]

16:12.873 --> 16:14.272
You know something,
Marcus?

16:14.274 --> 16:16.074
we're in the safety
of a parking lot.

16:16.076 --> 16:17.609
How would like
to take the wheel?

16:17.611 --> 16:21.146
Yo, for real? 'Cause I don't
have a license, Mr. Sweens.

16:21.148 --> 16:23.748
Well, what's that one thing
that Mr. Payton always says?

16:23.750 --> 16:24.883
Don't talk to cops.

16:24.885 --> 16:26.485
What? Does he
really say that to you?

16:26.487 --> 16:28.753
Yeah. Every day.
Call a lawyer first.

16:28.755 --> 16:30.622
No, I meant YOLO.

16:30.624 --> 16:33.425
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, he says that, too.

16:33.427 --> 16:36.561
Well, Marcus...
take the wheel.

16:36.563 --> 16:37.896
YOLO.

16:37.898 --> 16:39.698
You don't think
he believes in pussy power?

16:39.700 --> 16:43.101
I do not think that Joseph
believes in pussy power!
Joseph does! He --

16:43.103 --> 16:45.437
And I don't recall
there ever being

16:45.439 --> 16:47.506
"Coexist" bumper stickers
on camels!

16:47.508 --> 16:49.441
Oh, so now you're bigoted
against camels?!

16:49.443 --> 16:51.844
-Billy Shoemaker.
-Oh!

16:51.846 --> 16:53.712
Hey, Tampa.
What are you doing here?

16:53.714 --> 16:56.248
Oh, hey! I heard you
sold our baby's name!

16:56.250 --> 16:58.783
No, no, no, no, no.
But just hear me out.

16:58.785 --> 17:00.452
I auctioned the name.

17:00.454 --> 17:01.920
He probably
doesn't even remember.

17:01.922 --> 17:03.255
-He was hammered.
-Oh, of course you were.

17:03.257 --> 17:04.989
Oh! Thank you, Abbey.

17:04.991 --> 17:06.925
♪♪

17:06.927 --> 17:08.193
I got to tell you,
Fairbell.

17:08.195 --> 17:10.262
I think we really got
a shot with this.

17:10.264 --> 17:11.530
Whatever.

17:11.532 --> 17:12.997
You're not still upset

17:12.999 --> 17:14.399
about that stupid
Rocky Dennis doll, are you?

17:14.401 --> 17:16.134
Hey! It wasn't
a stupid doll, okay?

17:16.136 --> 17:18.336
He was number-one toy bud,
and I sold him.

17:18.338 --> 17:21.005
Look at this way, Fairbell --
If you're extra good this year,

17:21.007 --> 17:23.408
maybe Santa will
bring you a new one, huh?

17:23.410 --> 17:25.477
Loren, I'm 52 years old.

17:25.479 --> 17:26.811
I know how Santa works.

17:26.813 --> 17:29.081
-You're 52 years old?
-The news is here!

17:29.083 --> 17:31.216
-Burt Crandall!
-Here's here!

17:31.218 --> 17:32.417
-Burt! Burt Crandall!
-The news is here!

17:32.419 --> 17:33.618
-Burt!
-Oh, my God!

17:33.620 --> 17:36.020
Hi, trusted meteorologist
Burt Crandall. Hi.

17:36.022 --> 17:37.689
This is
an absolute pleasure.

17:37.691 --> 17:39.692
I am
Principal Geoffrey Quinn.

17:39.694 --> 17:42.160
Okay.
Let me know if
I can get you anything --

17:42.162 --> 17:44.496
eggnog, maybe some
gingerbread cookies.

17:44.498 --> 17:45.830
[ Chuckles ]

17:45.832 --> 17:48.166
I'd love a bourbon poured
over another bourbon.

17:48.168 --> 17:49.568
Mr. Crandall, I wanted
to let you know,

17:49.570 --> 17:51.169
this entire display

17:51.171 --> 17:53.572
is dedicated to a very special
young man named Marcus

17:53.574 --> 17:55.307
who needs a transplant
for his pigeon heart.

17:55.309 --> 17:57.776
Wait. They're giving
a kid a pigeon's heart?

17:57.778 --> 17:59.111
No, no, no, no, no.

17:59.113 --> 18:00.913
He has a very small heart
that we call a pigeon heart,

18:00.915 --> 18:02.380
but he needs
an actual human-sized --

18:02.382 --> 18:03.848
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay, okay. I get it.

18:03.850 --> 18:05.517
All right.
You three, scram.

18:05.519 --> 18:07.185
-Santa, stay.
-Okay.

18:07.187 --> 18:10.054
-Fred, I need my mic.
-I'm not Fred.

18:10.056 --> 18:11.189
Whatever.

18:11.191 --> 18:14.192
Yo! Mr. Sweens,

18:14.194 --> 18:16.929
hey, those Japanese fools know
what they're talking about.

18:16.931 --> 18:19.598
Well, just wait until
you discover green teas.

18:19.600 --> 18:22.667
Hoo! It's getting cold.

18:22.669 --> 18:26.071
You know something?
I'm gonna give you this.

18:26.073 --> 18:27.739
Oh, for real?

18:27.741 --> 18:30.008
Oh, yeah. Oh, man!

18:30.010 --> 18:31.076
♪♪

18:31.078 --> 18:32.344
All right, Marcus.

18:32.346 --> 18:35.547
[ Coughs ]
See you later.

18:35.549 --> 18:38.550
-Oh, yo, Mr. Sweens --
-YOLO, Marcus!

18:38.552 --> 18:39.885
YOLO.

18:42.156 --> 18:44.289
Thanks, Mr. Sweens.

18:44.291 --> 18:45.690
-That's all I was saying!
-That's all we wanted!

18:45.692 --> 18:48.360
I know, but I just feel like
you were pushing me, and...

18:48.362 --> 18:50.295
[ Clearing throat ]

18:50.297 --> 18:52.897
-And we're rolling.
-[ Chuckling ] Hey, hey, hey.

18:52.899 --> 18:54.967
Burt Crandall,
live at Smoot High,

18:54.969 --> 18:57.836
where this year's display
carries a special message --

18:57.838 --> 18:59.304
the hope
of a heart transplant

18:59.306 --> 19:01.373
for a young student
named Marcus.

19:01.375 --> 19:03.708
[ Chuckles ]

19:03.710 --> 19:05.510
Principal Quail,
let's see those lights.

19:05.512 --> 19:08.112
[ Laughing ] Okay.
Here we go.

19:08.114 --> 19:10.248
3...2...1.

19:10.250 --> 19:13.585
[ Slow festive music plays ]

19:13.587 --> 19:15.654
-Whoo!
-Whoa!

19:15.656 --> 19:17.522
-[ Chuckling ] Wow!
-God.

19:17.524 --> 19:19.591
-Oh!
-Wow!

19:19.593 --> 19:22.727
-Look at that!
-Oh!

19:22.729 --> 19:24.729
-That's so beautiful!
-Ohhh!

19:24.731 --> 19:27.199
-Billy! Billy! My water broke!
-Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

19:27.201 --> 19:28.933
Oh, my God!
Okay, okay!
Oh, my God.

19:28.935 --> 19:30.602
Okay.
Everybody stay calm!

19:30.604 --> 19:32.805
Why don't you sit down?
I'm a former doula!

19:32.807 --> 19:35.273
Oh, my God!
Is there a doctor?

19:35.275 --> 19:37.141
-Okay.
-Someone call a doctor!

19:37.143 --> 19:39.211
[ Chuckling ] Oh, my.
That's fantastic!

19:39.213 --> 19:40.545
Y-Yeah! Yeah.

19:40.547 --> 19:43.148
-You're poppin' out a baby.
-Yeah.

19:43.150 --> 19:45.550
These are actors
or real people?

19:45.552 --> 19:48.553
They are adult educators.
Okay.

19:48.555 --> 19:50.088
Well, they're teaching me
how to be human.

19:50.090 --> 19:52.290
Yeah.
Billy: [ In distance ] You
don't know what you're doing!

19:52.292 --> 19:53.425
-I just really --
-You're gonna push.

19:53.427 --> 19:54.626
-No, don't push!
-You're gonna push!

19:54.628 --> 19:56.294
-Oh, my God!
-You're gonna push!

19:56.296 --> 19:58.563
That birth looks
so realistic!

19:58.565 --> 20:00.499
It looks real. I mean...
Yeah, the entire scene
is very accurate.

20:00.501 --> 20:03.702
It's great. I mean,
it's like nativity on steroids.

20:03.704 --> 20:05.370
♪♪

20:05.372 --> 20:07.639
You know, guys,
I know I've been a skeptic,

20:07.641 --> 20:08.973
but, tonight,

20:08.975 --> 20:11.309
Smoot really made me
believe in something again.

20:11.311 --> 20:12.777
All right, guys.
Let's clear out.

20:12.779 --> 20:14.046
I got a report to do.

20:14.048 --> 20:17.315
♪♪

20:17.317 --> 20:20.853
Folks, in my 23 years
of holiday reporting,

20:20.855 --> 20:22.521
this display takes the cake.

20:22.523 --> 20:23.788
[ All breathing rhythmically ]
From the gorgeous lights

20:23.790 --> 20:26.859
to the amniotic fluid
in the manger, spot-on.

20:26.861 --> 20:28.193
It reminds us all

20:28.195 --> 20:31.530
that holiday truly is the season
of coincidences.

20:31.532 --> 20:32.997
Billy: Holy Jesus!

20:32.999 --> 20:34.533
I'm Burt Crandall.

20:34.535 --> 20:37.001
[ Horn honks ]
Marcus: Yo!
See you later, Sucktown!

20:37.003 --> 20:39.003
[ Tires screech ]
Oh, what was that?

20:39.005 --> 20:40.939
-Oh, wow.
-My Miata!

20:40.941 --> 20:42.675
Wait, my keys --
They were in the jacket.

20:42.677 --> 20:44.743
The keys were in the jacket!
Marcus stole my Miata!

20:44.745 --> 20:46.144
The pigeon kid
from the sign?

20:46.146 --> 20:47.479
No way.
What is this pigeon thing
that keeps coming up?

20:47.481 --> 20:49.214
That is clearly
a misunderstanding.

20:49.216 --> 20:51.416
[ Cellphone chimes ]
See? See? This is him
texting me right now.

20:51.418 --> 20:52.751
It says "YOLD."

20:52.753 --> 20:54.352
-What does "YOLD" mean?
-I don't know!

20:54.354 --> 20:55.487
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh, wait.
There's another one.

20:55.489 --> 20:57.089
-"YOKE"?
-Eggs.

20:57.091 --> 20:59.358
Yeah, maybe he's out
getting eggs or something.
Mm-hmm.

20:59.360 --> 21:00.959
-Okay, okay, okay.
-Okay.

21:00.961 --> 21:03.562
That was my bad.
I had that coming.
Get out of the way!

21:03.564 --> 21:05.497
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh, no,
here's another one. "YOYO"?

21:05.499 --> 21:06.899
He's racing
to buy yo-yos.

21:06.901 --> 21:07.900
-Oh!
-It's Christmas.

21:07.902 --> 21:09.634
You think
he's out buying yo-yos?

21:09.636 --> 21:11.904
-It's a classic gift.
-He could be buying yo--

21:11.906 --> 21:13.772
Oh, here's another one.
This is longer.

21:13.774 --> 21:16.040
"Damn autocorrect
got me thinking

21:16.042 --> 21:19.043
'bout switchin' to Samsung,
for real though."

21:19.045 --> 21:20.379
-Okay. Okay.
-Oh, my God, what is that?

21:20.381 --> 21:21.780
-Oh, God.
-Okay.

21:21.782 --> 21:22.915
He shouldn't
be texting and driving.

21:22.917 --> 21:24.116
He should keep
his eyes on the road!

21:24.118 --> 21:25.584
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh! YOLO!

21:25.586 --> 21:27.051
Together: Oh!
That's what
he's trying to text.

21:27.053 --> 21:28.186
Makes a lot of sense.

21:28.188 --> 21:29.922
-I always encourage him to YOLO.
-Yes.

21:29.924 --> 21:32.190
And the texts just
abruptly stopped, so he's fine.
Wait. What?

21:32.192 --> 21:34.993
I'm just getting word
of a horrific car crash.

21:34.995 --> 21:37.396
-Oh, no.
-Involving a Mini.

21:37.398 --> 21:39.998
-Oh, thank God.
-Scratch that -- a Miata.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
-Ohh!
-Oh, snap, bro.

21:42.002 --> 21:42.935
Damn it!

21:42.937 --> 21:46.605
It's a girl!
It's a baby girl!

21:46.607 --> 21:47.672
Ah! Oh!

21:47.674 --> 21:49.375
Ohh!
I wish it was a boy.

21:52.879 --> 21:54.146
[<i> Woman speaking indistinctly</i>
<i> over P.A.</i> ]

21:54.148 --> 21:57.215
All right, I've got
some information.
Okay.

21:57.217 --> 21:59.217
The good news
is Marcus is okay.

21:59.219 --> 22:00.552
-Yes!
-All right.

22:00.554 --> 22:01.886
-Oh, that's great!
-That is great news.

22:01.888 --> 22:04.889
Yeah. The bad news is he was
speeding and texting,

22:04.891 --> 22:07.092
jumped a curb, and ended up
killing a pedestrian.

22:07.094 --> 22:08.560
-Oh, my God. That's terrible.
-That is bad news.

22:08.562 --> 22:11.563
But the good news is the
pedestrian was an organ donor

22:11.565 --> 22:14.633
and an exact match
for his heart transplant.

22:14.635 --> 22:16.769
-That's pretty good news.
-That's really good.

22:16.771 --> 22:18.971
But the bad news is,
Marcus is going to jail

22:18.973 --> 22:20.905
without question
for quite a long time.

22:20.907 --> 22:23.642
He was, uh,
not cooperating with the police.

22:23.644 --> 22:24.909
That's pretty bad news.

22:24.911 --> 22:26.779
But the good news is

22:26.781 --> 22:29.381
the state now has to pay
for his operation.

22:29.383 --> 22:31.183
-That's pretty good news.
-[ Chuckling ] Okay.

22:31.185 --> 22:33.118
Oh, and, also,
the pedestrian he hit

22:33.120 --> 22:34.787
was our lunch lady,
Sandy.

22:34.789 --> 22:36.188
I didn't know
if that was like

22:36.190 --> 22:37.656
a good news or a bad news
kind of thing.

22:37.658 --> 22:39.324
She was the only one
who ever listened to me.

22:39.326 --> 22:40.459
Loren: I know.
That woman was as cold
as the food she served.

22:40.461 --> 22:41.526
It's like,
"Give me another scoop.

22:41.528 --> 22:43.061
It's not your money,
Sandy."
Yeah.

22:43.063 --> 22:45.063
-It's like, "Get over yourself."
-Right.

22:45.065 --> 22:46.731
Anyways,
we've got the prize money,

22:46.733 --> 22:49.401
so we could put that towards
Marcus' legal defense...

22:49.403 --> 22:53.271
I feel like
we've done enough for Marcus.

22:53.273 --> 22:55.808
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Fairbell, here you are.

22:55.810 --> 22:58.343
Hey, I sold that creepy
little doll of yours

22:58.345 --> 23:00.012
for 10 grand online!

23:00.014 --> 23:01.413
Is that fantastic?

23:01.415 --> 23:05.117
So I got you this.
A little thank-you gift.

23:06.753 --> 23:08.153
Ugh.

23:08.155 --> 23:10.555
-Oh, God.
-Don't you like it?

23:10.557 --> 23:11.690
Like it?

23:11.692 --> 23:12.757
[ Chuckling ] I love it!

23:12.759 --> 23:14.226
-All right!
-Cuddle bud!

23:14.228 --> 23:15.293
Get it away from me!

23:15.295 --> 23:17.162
Get it away!
Get it away!

23:17.164 --> 23:19.297
-Fairbell. Fairbell!
-No! No!

23:19.299 --> 23:20.699
Get that away from Tammy!
Get --
[ Door opens ]

23:20.701 --> 23:22.501
Hey. Guys.

23:22.503 --> 23:23.768
Together: Aww!

23:23.770 --> 23:25.838
I wanted to introduce you

23:25.840 --> 23:29.508
to the newest member
of the Shoemaker family.

23:29.510 --> 23:30.509
Aww.

23:30.511 --> 23:32.244
That's little baby

23:32.246 --> 23:34.913
Dealin' Dave
Chrysler-Jeep-Kia.

23:34.915 --> 23:36.181
Yeah. Yeah.

23:36.183 --> 23:38.917
And I want to thank you,
Abbey, for all your help.

23:38.919 --> 23:42.187
This truly is the greatest
Christmas gift of them all.

23:42.189 --> 23:44.789
[ Chuckles ]
Holiday.

23:44.791 --> 23:47.192
The greatest<i> holiday</i>
gift of all.

23:47.194 --> 23:48.126
Thank you.

23:48.128 --> 23:50.395
Great!
I'm being sued.

23:50.397 --> 23:51.463
They don't consider
the car stolen

23:51.465 --> 23:52.865
because I actually
gave Marcus the keys.

23:52.867 --> 23:54.733
Well, that's why I keep
saying YOLO, Steven.

23:54.735 --> 23:55.868
You know,
you only live once,

23:55.870 --> 23:58.270
so it's important
to do so very carefully.

23:58.272 --> 24:01.339
Anchor:<i> Coming up, Smoot High</i>
<i> back in the cross hairs</i>

24:01.341 --> 24:05.077
<i> as a guidance counselor puts</i>
<i> a 15-year-old behind the wheel</i>

24:05.079 --> 24:07.880
<i> of a candy apple red</i>
<i> soft-top street missile,</i>

24:07.882 --> 24:10.082
<i> taking the life</i>
<i> of a beloved lunch lady.</i>

24:10.084 --> 24:12.684
<i> All this</i>
<i> on the same night they win</i>

24:12.686 --> 24:14.553
<i> what will now be</i>
<i> the final edition</i>

24:14.555 --> 24:15.888
<i> of Burt Crandall's</i>

24:15.890 --> 24:18.557
<i> "12 Weeks of Holiday Lights"</i>
<i> contest.</i>

24:18.559 --> 24:20.492
<i> Was it your child</i>
<i> driving the car?</i>

24:20.494 --> 24:22.294
<i> Find out after the break.</i>

24:22.296 --> 24:23.695
[ Baby crying ]
Together: Aww!

24:23.697 --> 24:25.430
Oh, oh!

24:25.432 --> 24:27.099
This truly is...

24:27.101 --> 24:28.233
[ Crying continues ]
[ Festive music plays ]

24:28.235 --> 24:31.303
...a Smoot Holiday Coincidence.

24:31.305 --> 24:32.871
♪♪
